Coercive power tactics: Threatening or punishing people to persuade them. Power strategies include: Ultimatums Threats Punishment Retaliation Embargoes Reward power tactics: Rewarding or promising prizes to persuade others. Incentive power methods Promotions Bonuses Recognition\sPerks Legitimate power tactics: Using official authority or position to influence others. Position Job Title Rank are power strategies. Formalities Regulations Referent power tactics: Influencing people using personal traits or connections. Power methods include charisma, Expertise Trust\sLikability Connections Informational power techniques: These strategies employ knowledge to persuade. Facts are power tactics. Expert Analysis Info Control These power methods work differently depending on the situation and target. The leader should also evaluate the ethics of dominance methods and their possible drawbacks. 